Round Robin is a preemptive CPU scheduling algorithm mainly used in time-sharing systems. Each process gets a fixed time called Time Quantum (TQ).The CPU executes a process for one time quantum.
If the process is not finished, it goes to the end of the ready queue.

Steps of Round Robin
Enter number of processes.
Enter burst time for each process.
Enter time quantum.
Each process executes for the given time quantum.
If burst time > time quantum → process returns to queue.
Continue until all processes finish.
